criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Is age 18 years, on Study Day 0 with legal identification documents, and plan to live
             in the area during the study;

          2. Category III rabies exposure within 24 hours before Study Drug receipt ;

          3. Completed written informed consent process, and signed the informed consent forms;

          4. Agreed to complete all follow-ups;

          5. Female subjects are not in pregnancy (with negative results of urine pregnancy tests
             before vaccination) and are not in the period of breast feeding, and agree to avoid
             pregnancy within 6 months after administration;

          6. Those who have an armpit temperature ≤ 37.0 °C.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. After inquiry, previous receipt of equine or human (rabies) globulin or rabies
             vaccination.;

          2. After inquiry, History of bitten by animals, such as dog, cat, mongoose, fox, ferret,
             skunk, bat or raccoon (with skin damage), within the 6 months before Study Day 0

          3. Category I and Category II rabies exposure ;

          4. History of Category III rabies exposure and received wound suture treatment;

          5. Had fever (armpit temperature ≥ 38.5 °C) within 3 days before Study Day 0, or in the
             acute episode of any chronic diseases, or received any antipyretic, analgesic or
             anti-allergic drug within 3 days before enrollment;

          6. After inquiry, history of receiving any immunoglobulin or blood product within 45 days
             before Study Day 0, or plan to use any such product during the study;

          7. After inquiry, history of receiving systemic immunosuppressive therapy within 45 days
             before Study Day 0 such as long-term glucocorticoid treatment (period: ≥ 14 days;
             dosage: ≥ 20 mg /kg/day);

          8. After inquiry, History of any severe congenital defects or autoimmune disease (for
             example: AIDS, systemic lupus erythematosus, etc.), severe cardiovascular, liver or
             kidney disorders;

          9. After inquiry, history of asplenia or functional asplenia;

         10. History of any severe allergy for vaccination, such as systemic urticaria, allergic
             laryngeal edema, anaphylactoid purpura, local allergic necrosis (Arthus reaction),
             angioedema, anaphylactic shock, etc., or allergic to any ingredient of the study
             drug/vaccine;

         11. History of any severe neurological disease (Guillain-Barre syndrome, etc.);

         12. History or a family history of convulsion, epilepsy, encephalopathy or mental illness;

         13. After inquiry, Contraindication to intramuscular injection (diagnosed with any
             coagulopathy or received anticoagulant therapy);

         14. After inquiry, history of receiving any subunit or inactivated vaccine, such as
             pneumococcal vaccine, within 7 days before Study Day 0;

         15. After inquiry, history of receiving any live attenuated vaccine within 14 days before
             Study Day 1;

         16. After inquiry, history of addiction to any narcotic, alcohol or drugs;

         17. After inquiry, Previous receipt of any study product (drug, vaccine, biological
             product or device) within 6 months before Study Day 0, or plan to participate in any
             other clinical study during this study period;

         18. After inquiry, previous medical history that may affect the evaluation in this trial
             in the opinion of the investigators.
